entry.title: The South London Healthcare National Health Service Trust (Extension of Time for Trust Special Administrator to Provide a Draft Report) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order makes provision for an extension of the period within which the trust special administrator appointed for the South London Healthcare National Health Service Trust must provide a draft report to the Secretary of State. The period is extended by 30 working days from 45 working days beginning with the day on which the administrator's appointment takes effect to 75 working days from that date.

entry.title: The Indication of Prices (Beds) (Revocation) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order revokes the Indication of Prices (Beds) Order 1978 (S.I. 1978/1716, amended by S.I. 1979/364). The Indication of Prices (Beds) Order 1978 prohibited any person who indicated that a bed was or may be for sale by him from indicating a price at which that bed may be sold by another person. Some of its provisions lapsed following repeal, by the Competition Act 1980 (c.21), of the Price Commission Act 1977 (c.33) under which such provisions were made.

entry.title: The Royal Wolverhampton Hospitals National Health Service Trust (Establishment) Amendment Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order amends The Royal Wolverhampton Hospitals National Health Service Trust (Establishment) Order 1993 (“the Establishment Order”), which established The Royal Wolverhampton Hospitals National Health Service Trust.

entry.title: The Product Safety (Revocation) Regulations 2012
entry.summary: These Regulations revoke the instruments listed in the schedule.

entry.title: The Occupational Pension Schemes (Disclosure of Information) (Amendment) Regulations 2012
entry.summary: These regulations make amendments to the Occupational Pension Schemes (Disclosure of Information) Regulations 1996 (S.I. 1996/1655) to take account of the introduction of automatic enrolment of employees in a pension scheme by employers, which is provided for in Part 1 of the Pensions Act 2008 (c.30).

entry.title: The Broadcasting (Local Digital Television Programme Services and Independent Productions) (Amendment) Order 2012

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Broadcasting (Local Digital Television Programme Services and Independent Productions) (Amendment) Order 2012

entry.summary: This Order amends two previous Orders:

entry.title: The Social Fund Maternity Grant Amendment Regulations 2012
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Social Fund Maternity and Funeral Expenses (General) Regulations 2005 (S.I.2005/3061) and make necessary transitional provision.

entry.title: The Occupational and Personal Pension Schemes (Prescribed Bodies) Regulations 2012
entry.summary: These Regulations update references to the prescribed body in a number of occupational and personal pension schemes regulations as a consequence of the dissolution of the Board for Actuarial Standards (a former operating body of the Financial Reporting Council) and the Financial Reporting Council becoming directly responsible for issuing and maintaining technical actuarial standards and related functions.

entry.title: The Further Education Loans Regulations 2012
entry.summary: These Regulations provide for fee loans for students taking designated further education courses which begin on or after 1st September 2013.

entry.title: The Health and Social Care Act 2012 (Commencement No.2 and Transitional, Savings and Transitory Provisions) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order brings into force provisions of the Health and Social Care Act 2012 (c. 7) (“the Act”). It is the second Commencement Order to be made under the Act. This Order also contains transitional, savings and transitory provisions in relation to the provisions of the Act being brought into force by this Order.

entry.title: The Armed Forces Act (Continuation) Order 2012
entry.summary: Section 382(2) of the Armed Forces Act 2006 (“the 2006 Act”) provides that the 2006 Act will expire at the end of one year beginning with the day on which the Armed Forces Act 2011 (“the 2011 Act”) was passed unless continued in force by Order in Council in accordance with that section. The 2011 Act was passed on 3rd November 2011.

entry.title: The Local Authorities (Armorial Bearings) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order authorises Ludlow Town Council to bear and use the armorial bearings formerly borne and used by the corporation of the Borough of Ludlow.

entry.title: The Consular Fees (Amendment) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order amends the Consular Fees Order 2012. The fees for passport applications made in the UK are being reduced by £5 for adult applications and by £3 for child applications. Fast track applications are reduced by £9.50. Premium and fast-track collect adult applications are reduced by £1.50. Premium and fast-track collect child applications are reduced by £3.00. There is no change to the fee for a collective passport.

entry.title: The Pitcairn (Court of Appeal) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order confers validity on the appointments of three judges of the Court of Appeal for Pitcairn, doubts about which had arisen. It also confers validity on all acts and things done by those judges in purported exercise of their offices.

entry.title: The Protection of Wrecks (Designation) (England) (No.2) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order designates as a restricted area for the purposes of the Protection of Wrecks Act 1973 an area within 50 metres from the site of a vessel identified as “Goodwins and Downs 8” or “GAD8” lying in the Downs anchorage, 2.04 kilometres east of Deal, Kent.

entry.title: The Copyright (Repeal of the Copyright Act 1911) (Jersey) Order 2012
entry.summary: The Intellectual Property (Unregistered Rights) (Jersey) Law 2011 received Royal Assent on 16th November 2011 and will be brought into force in accordance with provision made under it. The provisions of Part 1 of the 2011 Law will replace those contained in the Copyright Act 1911. The provisions of the 1911 Act are maintained in force in Jersey by virtue of paragraph 36 of Schedule 1 to the Copyright, Designs and Patents Act 1988 notwithstanding the repeal of the 1911 Act in the United Kingdom. This Order repeals the Copyright Act 1911 as it applies to Jersey on the day on which Part 1 of the Intellectual Property (Unregistered Rights) (Jersey) Law 2011 is brought into force in its entirety.

entry.title: The Income Tax (Exemption of Minor Benefits) (Amendment) Regulations 2012
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Income Tax (Exemption of Minor Benefits) Regulations 2002 (S.I. 2002/205) (“the principal Regulations”) to remove as an exempt minor benefit food or drink provided by an employer to an employee in recognition of the employee having cycled from home to the workplace on designated days. The exemption is removed with effect from 6th April 2013.

entry.title: The Copyright and Performances (Application to Other Countries) (Amendment) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order amends the Copyright and Performances (Application to Other Countries) Order 2012 (S.I.2012/799).

entry.title: The Immigration (Jersey) Order 2012
entry.summary: This Order extends to Jersey, with modifications, sections 31, 32, 34 and 39 of the Immigration, Asylum and Nationality Act 2006. It also further modifies section 18 of the Immigration and Asylum Act 1999 which was previously extended to Jersey with modifications by the Immigration and Asylum Act (Jersey) Order 2003 (SI 2003/1252).

entry.title: The Housing (Right to Manage) (England) Regulations 2012
entry.summary: These Regulations, which are made under sections 27 and 27AB of the Housing Act 1985, set out the procedure to be followed where a tenant management organisation (“TMO”) proposes to enter into a management agreement with a local housing authority under section 27 of that Act. The Regulations impose an obligation on the authority in specified circumstances to enter into a management agreement, and contain related provisions.
